\headright{Role Descriptions}

\smaller{As the Sole DevOps Engineer, it was my responsibility to maintain the Azure environment from Kubernetes clusters, to migration off the cluster and various VM's we use. Then Migrating from a Jenkins instance and jenkinsfiles over to Github and Actions. This required alot of rebuilding for automation scripts for the new setup. Then maintaining applications being hosted on our on-premise servers including MDM servers needing debugging and openssl machines for certificates. }

\is
\smaller{During my time as a DevOps Engineer to begin with I was a part of a DevOps team with the responsibility of maintaining multiple teams environments at once by updating them and deploying through terraform automation pipelines. Streamlining and optimizing the pipeline to increase success rate and reduce build time. Actively supporting the teams when they run into errors.}

\is
\smaller{As a Apprentice DevOps Engineer I was put through a bootcamp to learn the fundamentals of DevOps and then assigned a team to further knowledge, My responsibilities includes periodic activities such as updating docker images and plugins throughout environments and ensuring they don't cause breaking changes by testing and then deploying these to the production cluster. Taking on a wide range of different tickets such as Linux on premise servers updating and setup for hosting Jenkins on.}

